---
import ContentLayout from '../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
---

<ContentLayout title="Contributing to SANE">
  <p>
    SANE is a fully open source project. Everything — the standards, data, tools, and this website —
    lives in a public GitHub repository. All contributions are welcome.
  </p>

  <h2>Ways to Contribute</h2>

  <h3>Propose a Standard (RFC)</h3>
  <p>
    Open a GitHub issue using the <strong>RFC template</strong>. Describe the problem, your
    proposed solution, and which AV domains are affected. See the <a href="/rfc">RFC Process</a>
    page for the full workflow.
  </p>

  <h3>Write or Improve Content</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Add or improve glossary terms in <code>src/content/glossary/</code></li>
    <li>Write a blog post in <code>src/content/blog/</code></li>
    <li>Submit a whitepaper in <code>src/content/whitepapers/</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Add Equipment Data</h3>
  <p>
    Add equipment specs as JSON entries in <code>src/data/equipment/</code>. Each file is a
    JSON array following the schema defined in <code>src/data/equipment/schema.json</code>.
    Open a PR with your additions or corrections.
  </p>

  <h3>Build a Tool</h3>
  <p>
    AV calculators live in <code>src/pages/tools/</code> as self-contained Astro pages with
    client-side JavaScript. No framework required — just HTML, CSS, and vanilla JS in the
    <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> block.
  </p>

  <h3>Fix Bugs or Improve the Site</h3>
  <p>
    The site is built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro</a>.
    Issues and PRs for design, accessibility, and performance improvements are very welcome.
  </p>

  <h2>Getting Started</h2>

  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/sane-av/sane-av.git
cd sane-av
npm install
npm run dev</code></pre>

  <p>The dev server starts at <code>http://localhost:4321</code>.</p>

  <h2>Commit & PR Guidelines</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Use clear, descriptive commit messages (e.g. <code>feat(glossary): add dBFS entry</code>)</li>
    <li>One logical change per PR — keep diffs small and reviewable</li>
    <li>For new standards, follow the RFC process before opening a content PR</li>
    <li>All content must be original or properly attributed under CC BY 4.0</li>
    <li>No vendor-specific content that favors proprietary products over open alternatives</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Code of Conduct</h2>
  <p>
    Be respectful and constructive. Technical disagreements are normal; personal attacks are not.
    SANE follows the <a href="https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/1/code_of_conduct/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Contributor Covenant v2.1</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>License</h2>
  <p>
    By contributing, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under
    <strong>MIT</strong> (code) and <strong>CC BY 4.0</strong> (content and data).
  </p>
</ContentLayout>
